HEADWORD: Hydriodide
<hw>Hy*dri"o*dide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A compound of hydriodic acid with a base; -- distinguished from an
<contr>iodide</contr>, in which only the iodine combines with the
base.</def></p>

